						<div class="postbody">I think you could cut that in half in a lot of cases.  There are lots of times where the duration, and especially the octave and instrument will remain unchanged between notes.  If you don't mind working with nybbles, you could just move on to the next nybble if the current one isn't D, E, or F.</div>

