					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You don't need 16 different command bytes for looping just one is enough, you place that byte followed by the adress to loop (if you're very concerned about ROM space : place only one byte that is how much you should substract to the current adress to get to the loop point, but you can only go 256 bytes backwards).</div>
<br />Yesterday, I implemented a conductor track into my own music engine. I use two commands: one to copy the current position to the loop point ("CON_SEGNO"), and one to copy the other way, jumping to the loop point ("CON_DALSEGNO"). (If you don't know what a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dal_Segno" class="postlink">segno</a> is, you can look it up.)</div>

