			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Tetramino defines its sound effects as 
<br />HEADER: 2 bytes, length and number of frames per step
<br />EACH ELEMENT: 2 bytes, duty+volume and pitch. But the way I specify pitch might not work for a platformer because it's limited to semitones.
<br />
<br />Right now, it uses a very simplistic, Game Boy-style instrument definition. Each instrument is 1 byte for duty+initial volume and 1 byte for decay rate. But I too am interested in what parameters I need to use to make it sound less Game Boy-ish.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

